## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="28887-104">La propriété ou le champ doit être public.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="28887-104">The property or field must be public.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="28887-105">La classe qui contient la propriété doit être marquée avec le <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementEntityAttribute> attribut.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="28887-105">The class that contains the property must be marked with the <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementEntityAttribute> attribute.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="28887-106">Tous les champs ou propriétés de la classe qui ne sont pas marquées avec ce ou un autre attribut d’Extensions fournisseur WMI ne seront pas instrumentées.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="28887-106">Any fields or properties in the class that are not marked with this or another WMI Provider Extensions attribute will not be instrumented.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="28887-107">L’exemple suivant montre comment utiliser l’attribut ManagementConfiguration pour marquer une propriété.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="28887-107">The following example shows how to use the ManagementConfiguration attribute to mark a property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="28887-108">Cette propriété est exposée dans WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="28887-108">This property is exposed to WMI.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Use the ManagementConfiguration attribute to specify that a property  
// is a read/write property in the provider. Consumers will be  
// able to get and set this property value through WMI.  
[ManagementConfiguration]  
public double ReadableWritableProperty  
{  
    get { return this.propertyValue; }  
    set { this.propertyValue = value; }  
}  
```
